grounding.caption: Increased bibasilar opacities consistent with worsening multifocal pneumonia.

Left subclavian central venous catheter
 terminates in the distal left brachiocephalic vein. Bilateral multifocal
 areas of consolidation show a slight interval improvement, and likely
 represent improving multifocal pneumonia. Coexisting linear atelectasis is
 present in the left mid lung region.
Moderate bilateral pleural effusions and associated atelectasis. More dense consolidation at the right lung base raises possibility of superimposed infection.
